Text.SourceString: Hello! I don’t think I’ve seen you before. Are you new in town?
Text.LocalizedString: Hello! I don’t think I’ve seen you before. Are you new in town?

Text.SourceString: See you around!
Text.LocalizedString: See you around!

Text.SourceString: We’re open every day. Weather permitting, that is.
Text.LocalizedString: We’re open every day. Weather permitting, that is.

Text.SourceString: What a beautiful day to be outdoors.//I might go to Garden Lane before work tomorrow to enjoy my morning beverage and look at the butterflies. Hmm…//<portrait=happy>No, yeah… I will definitely do that.
Text.LocalizedString: What a beautiful day to be outdoors.//I might go to Garden Lane before work tomorrow to enjoy my morning beverage and look at the butterflies. Hmm…//<portrait=happy>No, yeah… I will definitely do that.

Text.SourceString: I’m not too worried about how much the coffee shop makes. Creating the perfect cup of coffee is where my mind is.//Each individual cup. Yeah, every one is special.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not too worried about how much the coffee shop makes. Creating the perfect cup of coffee is where my mind is.//Each individual cup. Yeah, every one is special.

Text.SourceString: I can’t stand when people wear perfume that’s too strong.//It overwhelms my nose for the day, and I don’t like that.//I like to be able to smell the coffee.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t stand when people wear perfume that’s too strong.//It overwhelms my nose for the day, and I don’t like that.//I like to be able to smell the coffee.

Text.SourceString: Vegetables? As in <Italic>raw</> vegetables?//None for me, thanks. I’m not big on vegetables. Fruit, on the other hand…
Text.LocalizedString: Vegetables? As in <Italic>raw</> vegetables?//None for me, thanks. I’m not big on vegetables. Fruit, on the other hand…

Text.SourceString: Now, now. It doesn’t mean I don’t eat my vegetables, ’cause I do.//I do! Seriously!//I just don’t do it for fun. Or have more than the recommended amount.
Text.LocalizedString: Now, now. It doesn’t mean I don’t eat my vegetables, ’cause I do.//I do! Seriously!//I just don’t do it for fun. Or have more than the recommended amount.

Text.SourceString: The coffee maker at the shop is weather resistant.//It can withstand rain – snow even!//It was costly but worth every penny.
Text.LocalizedString: The coffee maker at the shop is weather resistant.//It can withstand rain – snow even!//It was costly but worth every penny.

Text.SourceString: My hair gets sticky fast latly. Kinda hate it. Is yours that way too?
Text.LocalizedString: My hair gets sticky fast latly. Kinda hate it. Is yours that way too?

Text.SourceString: The beach isn’t the place to sell coffee. Not freshly brewed, anyway. In cans, yeah, maybe! //<portrait=sad>At the beach, with the wind blowing sand all over… Yeah, no.
Text.LocalizedString: The beach isn’t the place to sell coffee. Not freshly brewed, anyway. In cans, yeah, maybe! //<portrait=sad>At the beach, with the wind blowing sand all over… Yeah, no.

Text.SourceString: For Spring, I usually go for a coffee with floral notes. It seems fitting for the season.
Text.LocalizedString: For Spring, I usually go for a coffee with floral notes. It seems fitting for the season.

Text.SourceString: The coffee shop opened as usual in Winter.//But we closed when it got too cold. Thankfully, those days are behind us now.
Text.LocalizedString: The coffee shop opened as usual in Winter.//But we closed when it got too cold. Thankfully, those days are behind us now.

Text.SourceString: Coffee beans from different regions taste different. Things like soil and weather have an impact.//Correct me if I’m wrong, but I don’t think you can grow <Italic>good</> coffee beans right now, right? In Spring?
Text.LocalizedString: Coffee beans from different regions taste different. Things like soil and weather have an impact.//Correct me if I’m wrong, but I don’t think you can grow <Italic>good</> coffee beans right now, right? In Spring?

Text.SourceString: Not at all, huh? Yeah, that sounds about right.//I didn’t think you could grow coffee here in Spring, not in this weather. Yeah, no.
Text.LocalizedString: Not at all, huh? Yeah, that sounds about right.//I didn’t think you could grow coffee here in Spring, not in this weather. Yeah, no.

Text.SourceString: Will you be planting coffee this Summer?
Text.LocalizedString: Will you be planting coffee this Summer?

Text.SourceString: So, are you the type of person who drinks hot coffee in Summer?
Text.LocalizedString: So, are you the type of person who drinks hot coffee in Summer?

Text.SourceString: That’s what I’m talking about!
Text.LocalizedString: That’s what I’m talking about!

Text.SourceString: I prefer to brew locally grown beans, of course, but yeah, no. There isn’t much choice, unfortunately.//We can only plant coffee here in Summer. So that means I have to import some of my beans.
Text.LocalizedString: I prefer to brew locally grown beans, of course, but yeah, no. There isn’t much choice, unfortunately.//We can only plant coffee here in Summer. So that means I have to import some of my beans.

Text.SourceString: I don’t drink coffee every day. Yeah, no.//I do enjoy the many different flavors each cup offers. Always a great experience. A mood booster.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t drink coffee every day. Yeah, no.//I do enjoy the many different flavors each cup offers. Always a great experience. A mood booster.

Text.SourceString: I think Summer is perfect for coffee with citrus notes. Doesn’t Summer feel like a citrusy season to you?
Text.LocalizedString: I think Summer is perfect for coffee with citrus notes. Doesn’t Summer feel like a citrusy season to you?

Text.SourceString: I pay attention to when my customers prefer to have their coffee, and of course, their favorite blend.//For instance, the astrophysicist, <NPCName>Wakuu</>, likes his coffee in the afternoon, and <NPCName>Aaliyah</> likes it early in the morning.//Yeah, she’s the military pilot. Was or is – not sure.
Text.LocalizedString: I pay attention to when my customers prefer to have their coffee, and of course, their favorite blend.//For instance, the astrophysicist, <NPCName>Wakuu</>, likes his coffee in the afternoon, and <NPCName>Aaliyah</> likes it early in the morning.//Yeah, she’s the military pilot. Was or is – not sure.

Text.SourceString: Have you seen the daisies? I’m so tempted to put some in my beard!
Text.LocalizedString: Have you seen the daisies? I’m so tempted to put some in my beard!

Text.SourceString: There’s something about drinking hot chocolate in Fall, isn’t there?//Something special about it.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s something about drinking hot chocolate in Fall, isn’t there?//Something special about it.

Text.SourceString: Every once in a while, I create a coffee omakase, usually in Fall.//I taste-test my favorite combos of the year before putting them on the menu.
Text.LocalizedString: Every once in a while, I create a coffee omakase, usually in Fall.//I taste-test my favorite combos of the year before putting them on the menu.

Text.SourceString: For Fall, you just gotta go with the classic cocoa and caramel notes in your coffee.//It’s perfect for this season.
Text.LocalizedString: For Fall, you just gotta go with the classic cocoa and caramel notes in your coffee.//It’s perfect for this season.

Text.SourceString: Have you ever tried cooking with dragon fruit, friend? It looks so dramatic, doesn’t it?//<portrait=annoyed>I’ve been trying to come up with a recipe for it, but I haven’t come up with anything good.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you ever tried cooking with dragon fruit, friend? It looks so dramatic, doesn’t it?//<portrait=annoyed>I’ve been trying to come up with a recipe for it, but I haven’t come up with anything good.

Text.SourceString: Being outdoors has its downside on days like this.
Text.LocalizedString: Being outdoors has its downside on days like this.

Text.SourceString: A warm drink for the day?
Text.LocalizedString: A warm drink for the day?

Text.SourceString: Some people are immune to Winter, it seems.//Saw <NPCName>Macy</> walking around in shorts the other day.//<portrait=happy>I was shocked. Impressed in a way, but yeah, no. I couldn’t do that. Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: Some people are immune to Winter, it seems.//Saw <NPCName>Macy</> walking around in shorts the other day.//<portrait=happy>I was shocked. Impressed in a way, but yeah, no. I couldn’t do that. Ha ha!

Text.SourceString: I don’t wear perfume or anything that’s strongly scented, especially when I’m making coffee or blending coffee beans.//Those scents can get into the beans.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t wear perfume or anything that’s strongly scented, especially when I’m making coffee or blending coffee beans.//Those scents can get into the beans.

Text.SourceString: The inn gets really cold in Winter.//<portrait=happy>Thank goodness for portable heaters.
Text.LocalizedString: The inn gets really cold in Winter.//<portrait=happy>Thank goodness for portable heaters.

Text.SourceString: Living at the inn is great, especially in Winter. It’s cold, and you just wanna hang out with friends.//Yeah, the inn is cold, and the heater is…questionable at times, but the residents are friendly.
Text.LocalizedString: Living at the inn is great, especially in Winter. It’s cold, and you just wanna hang out with friends.//Yeah, the inn is cold, and the heater is…questionable at times, but the residents are friendly.

Text.SourceString: This here is my coffee shop. Stop by whenever you feel the need for that jolt of caffeine!
Text.LocalizedString: This here is my coffee shop. Stop by whenever you feel the need for that jolt of caffeine!

Text.SourceString: I like the way I look now, and I’m comfortable with myself, but there was a time when I felt like I had to fit into certain boxes to appeal to others.
Text.LocalizedString: I like the way I look now, and I’m comfortable with myself, but there was a time when I felt like I had to fit into certain boxes to appeal to others.

Text.SourceString: Some people can be very…gatekeepy. Even those who claim to be open minded.
Text.LocalizedString: Some people can be very…gatekeepy. Even those who claim to be open minded.

Text.SourceString: I didn’t grow up drinking coffee. My family was more of a tea family. But I just find coffee more interesting, you know?//<portrait=happy>The taste, the brewing process, the roasting process, even how it’s grown and harvested. It’s much more interesting to me than tea.
Text.LocalizedString: I didn’t grow up drinking coffee. My family was more of a tea family. But I just find coffee more interesting, you know?//<portrait=happy>The taste, the brewing process, the roasting process, even how it’s grown and harvested. It’s much more interesting to me than tea.

Text.SourceString: I don’t like a lot of fuss for my morning coffee, so I’ll usually go for a French press.//Later in the day, I can go for something more complex, like a pour-over or an espresso.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t like a lot of fuss for my morning coffee, so I’ll usually go for a French press.//Later in the day, I can go for something more complex, like a pour-over or an espresso.

Text.SourceString: Oh, a good grinder is a must if you want delicious coffee. The really good ones can cost hundreds and thousands of coins.//<portrait=normal>For home use, just avoid using those blade grinders and stick to burr grinders. The hand-cranked ones are pretty good and not too expensive.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, a good grinder is a must if you want delicious coffee. The really good ones can cost hundreds and thousands of coins.//<portrait=normal>For home use, just avoid using those blade grinders and stick to burr grinders. The hand-cranked ones are pretty good and not too expensive.

Text.SourceString: Or – here’s an idea!//You can just stop by my coffee shop and skip all the hassle, yeah?
Text.LocalizedString: Or – here’s an idea!//You can just stop by my coffee shop and skip all the hassle, yeah?

Text.SourceString: As much as I love coffee, I also want to sell and consume it sustainably. Buy locally and all that.//<portrait=normal>Speaking of, do you grow coffee, and if so, can I buy some from you?
Text.LocalizedString: As much as I love coffee, I also want to sell and consume it sustainably. Buy locally and all that.//<portrait=normal>Speaking of, do you grow coffee, and if so, can I buy some from you?

Text.SourceString: I named my coffee shop after me. After my full name.//<portrait=normal>Ha ha! No, yeah. Truth! My full name is <NPCName>Raja</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I named my coffee shop after me. After my full name.//<portrait=normal>Ha ha! No, yeah. Truth! My full name is <NPCName>Raja</>.

Text.SourceString: It means “King.” No, yeah. Seriously.
Text.LocalizedString: It means “King.” No, yeah. Seriously.

Text.SourceString: Ha! That caught me off guard.//<portrait=normal>Thank you for the kind words.
Text.LocalizedString: Ha! That caught me off guard.//<portrait=normal>Thank you for the kind words.

Text.SourceString: The other time, you asked me if my name had any meaning. What about you, <PlayerName>$Player</>?//What does <PlayerName>$Player</> mean?
Text.LocalizedString: The other time, you asked me if my name had any meaning. What about you, <PlayerName>$Player</>?//What does <PlayerName>$Player</> mean?

Text.SourceString: Well, the name suits you.//<PlayerName>$Player</> is so you.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, the name suits you.//<PlayerName>$Player</> is so you.

Text.SourceString: Just like you. What a personality.
Text.LocalizedString: Just like you. What a personality.

Text.SourceString: Ah, so that’s not your given name.//<portrait=normal>It fits you. <PlayerName>$Player</> is a lovely name.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, so that’s not your given name.//<portrait=normal>It fits you. <PlayerName>$Player</> is a lovely name.

Special.SourceString: Well, I picked it because I liked the way it sounds.
Special.LocalizedString: Well, I picked it because I liked the way it sounds.

Text.SourceString: The coffee shop is closed when it’s raining like this. So I usually spend the day volunteering at the shelter.
Text.LocalizedString: The coffee shop is closed when it’s raining like this. So I usually spend the day volunteering at the shelter.

Text.SourceString: Out in the rain? Got a place to be?
Text.LocalizedString: Out in the rain? Got a place to be?

Text.SourceString: The coffee shop is closed when it’s raining like this. So I usually spend the day volunteering at the shelter.
Text.LocalizedString: The coffee shop is closed when it’s raining like this. So I usually spend the day volunteering at the shelter.

Text.SourceString: Out in the rain this late? Got someplace to be?
Text.LocalizedString: Out in the rain this late? Got someplace to be?

Text.SourceString: The coffee shop is closed when there’s a storm like this. So I usually spend the day volunteering at the shelter.
Text.LocalizedString: The coffee shop is closed when there’s a storm like this. So I usually spend the day volunteering at the shelter.

Text.SourceString: Out in the storm? Got someplace to be?
Text.LocalizedString: Out in the storm? Got someplace to be?

Text.SourceString: You’re out late today, and in the storm too.//<portrait=happy>Busy as usual, yeah? Nothing can slow you down.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re out late today, and in the storm too.//<portrait=happy>Busy as usual, yeah? Nothing can slow you down.

Text.SourceString: Busy as usual, yeah? No snow could slow you down.
Text.LocalizedString: Busy as usual, yeah? No snow could slow you down.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I’ll wear a hat next time. This snow gets my hair all wet.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I’ll wear a hat next time. This snow gets my hair all wet.

Text.SourceString: Do you like dinner parties, friend?//<portrait=normal>I can’t think of a better way to spend a cold night like this. Fine coffee, delicious food, warm convos. Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: Do you like dinner parties, friend?//<portrait=normal>I can’t think of a better way to spend a cold night like this. Fine coffee, delicious food, warm convos. Hmm…

Text.SourceString: The ladies at the inn – the twins, yeah? They let me decorate my room the way I want.//They’re very generous.
Text.LocalizedString: The ladies at the inn – the twins, yeah? They let me decorate my room the way I want.//They’re very generous.

Text.SourceString: They provide extra blankets too.//<portrait=annoyed>Not that we need them, though. In this heat? Yeah, no!
Text.LocalizedString: They provide extra blankets too.//<portrait=annoyed>Not that we need them, though. In this heat? Yeah, no!

Text.SourceString: The ladies at the inn are always so adventurous with their linens. On a Winter day like this not too long ago, I came home to tie-dyed sheets!//<portrait=happy>That was certainly <Italic>something</>.
Text.LocalizedString: The ladies at the inn are always so adventurous with their linens. On a Winter day like this not too long ago, I came home to tie-dyed sheets!//<portrait=happy>That was certainly <Italic>something</>.

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>, what sorts of things do you like to do when you’re not working?
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>, what sorts of things do you like to do when you’re not working?

Text.SourceString: Oh yeah? Are you good at it?//Pool’s one of those things I’d like to get better at, but I haven’t worked at it.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh yeah? Are you good at it?//Pool’s one of those things I’d like to get better at, but I haven’t worked at it.

Text.SourceString: Ahh. Of course. You strike me as the beach type.//<portrait=normal>Good taste. Myself, I prefer the garden, but who can resist the beach?
Text.LocalizedString: Ahh. Of course. You strike me as the beach type.//<portrait=normal>Good taste. Myself, I prefer the garden, but who can resist the beach?

Text.SourceString: Whew, is it hot or was my coffee too strong? Good gosh, it’s hot! I am <Italic>so</> wired today!//I tried out a new coffee blend, and it hit way harder than I expected!//Don’t think I’ve blinked in the past five minutes! Whew!
Text.LocalizedString: Whew, is it hot or was my coffee too strong? Good gosh, it’s hot! I am <Italic>so</> wired today!//I tried out a new coffee blend, and it hit way harder than I expected!//Don’t think I’ve blinked in the past five minutes! Whew!

Text.SourceString: I’m talking really fast!//I need to sit down.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m talking really fast!//I need to sit down.

Text.SourceString: I love people watching, so owning the coffee stand really is the best job for me.//<portrait=normal>I get to stand here all day and see people go by.
Text.LocalizedString: I love people watching, so owning the coffee stand really is the best job for me.//<portrait=normal>I get to stand here all day and see people go by.

Text.SourceString: Yeah, I get sore feet at the end of the day, but people are interesting. It’s worth it.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, I get sore feet at the end of the day, but people are interesting. It’s worth it.

Text.SourceString: When it’s humid, we expect angry clouds.//Beauty never arrives alone. There’s always a price attached.
Text.LocalizedString: When it’s humid, we expect angry clouds.//Beauty never arrives alone. There’s always a price attached.

Text.SourceString: There’s no such thing as weather that’s too hot for drinking hot beverages.//<portrait=annoyed>Drinking coffee is an <Italic>experience</>. You can’t just put <Italic>ice</> in it.//No! Ice waters down the flavor.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s no such thing as weather that’s too hot for drinking hot beverages.//<portrait=annoyed>Drinking coffee is an <Italic>experience</>. You can’t just put <Italic>ice</> in it.//No! Ice waters down the flavor.

Text.SourceString: I’m not one for seasonal drinks. I like a variety of coffee beans, but I don’t think I could bring myself to drink any of the stranger concoctions, like pumpkin lattes.//<portrait=annoyed>Yeah…no. The thing is I don’t think a lot of that stuff tastes good, when it comes to it.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not one for seasonal drinks. I like a variety of coffee beans, but I don’t think I could bring myself to drink any of the stranger concoctions, like pumpkin lattes.//<portrait=annoyed>Yeah…no. The thing is I don’t think a lot of that stuff tastes good, when it comes to it.

Text.SourceString: I also don’t like jamu, if that’s any indication.//<portrait=happy>What were we even talking about?
Text.LocalizedString: I also don’t like jamu, if that’s any indication.//<portrait=happy>What were we even talking about?

Text.SourceString: Since I can’t open my stand today, I figured I’d come down to the community center and see what’s going on.
Text.LocalizedString: Since I can’t open my stand today, I figured I’d come down to the community center and see what’s going on.

Text.SourceString: It’s hard to farm in the rain too, huh?//<portrait=happy>We can be bad-weather buddies!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s hard to farm in the rain too, huh?//<portrait=happy>We can be bad-weather buddies!

Text.SourceString: I think I should get some dog biscuits to keep on the counter.//<portrait=normal>So if people bring their dogs, they can have a treat too.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I should get some dog biscuits to keep on the counter.//<portrait=normal>So if people bring their dogs, they can have a treat too.

Text.SourceString: I saw Taco playing around the other day, enjoying the sunny Spring day in the fountain.//<portrait=happy>He sure knows how to have fun!
Text.LocalizedString: I saw Taco playing around the other day, enjoying the sunny Spring day in the fountain.//<portrait=happy>He sure knows how to have fun!

Text.SourceString: Oh gosh! I sure hope Taco was actually playing in that fountain and not…//Oh good gosh!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh gosh! I sure hope Taco was actually playing in that fountain and not…//Oh good gosh!

Text.SourceString: Is it too early to bust out my swimming trunks?//<portrait=normal>Ah, yeah. I can wait till Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: Is it too early to bust out my swimming trunks?//<portrait=normal>Ah, yeah. I can wait till Summer.

Text.SourceString: This place needs a good coffee shop.//It’s a complete waste to drink bad coffee. There’s only so many drinks you can have in a lifetime.//<portrait=sad>Ah, very limited. I pity anybody who doesn’t have access to a good brew.
Text.LocalizedString: This place needs a good coffee shop.//It’s a complete waste to drink bad coffee. There’s only so many drinks you can have in a lifetime.//<portrait=sad>Ah, very limited. I pity anybody who doesn’t have access to a good brew.

Text.SourceString: It’s way too snowy to open the coffee stand.//<portrait=normal>Better stay in close to the fireplace.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s way too snowy to open the coffee stand.//<portrait=normal>Better stay in close to the fireplace.

Text.SourceString: When the snow stops, we can open the coffee shop again, but not now, not today.//Today we relax and give back.
Text.LocalizedString: When the snow stops, we can open the coffee shop again, but not now, not today.//Today we relax and give back.

Text.SourceString: I want to do something fun this Summer.//<portrait=normal>I’m thinking beach day every day!
Text.LocalizedString: I want to do something fun this Summer.//<portrait=normal>I’m thinking beach day every day!

Text.SourceString: That’s what Summer is for!
Text.LocalizedString: That’s what Summer is for!

Text.SourceString: <Italic>Iced coffee?</> What do you mean, iced coffee?//Yeah, no. We don’t do iced coffee.
Text.LocalizedString: <Italic>Iced coffee?</> What do you mean, iced coffee?//Yeah, no. We don’t do iced coffee.

Text.SourceString: Have you seen the cats? Where are those cats?//<portrait=annoyed>The orange one! I think the orange cat kicked over a whole sack of beans yesterday!
Text.LocalizedString: Have you seen the cats? Where are those cats?//<portrait=annoyed>The orange one! I think the orange cat kicked over a whole sack of beans yesterday!

Text.SourceString: I know what I saw, okay? The other day, I saw that cat and the other one playing around with the sack of beans.//<portrait=angry>Tried to shoo it nicely, but obviously, it didn’t work. I came in, and there were beans all over the floor!
Text.LocalizedString: I know what I saw, okay? The other day, I saw that cat and the other one playing around with the sack of beans.//<portrait=angry>Tried to shoo it nicely, but obviously, it didn’t work. I came in, and there were beans all over the floor!

Text.SourceString: I can’t rely on shipping by sea here.//<portrait=angry>I ordered some coffee beans from San Franciskyo. They were supposed to be here by now, but no cargo boats are coming until next week.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t rely on shipping by sea here.//<portrait=angry>I ordered some coffee beans from San Franciskyo. They were supposed to be here by now, but no cargo boats are coming until next week.

Text.SourceString: What am I supposed to do? I heard <NpcName>Ben</> can get you the good stuff, even rare finds, but he doesn’t travel much anymore.//I can’t run my business based on <NpcName>Ben’s</> moods.
Text.LocalizedString: What am I supposed to do? I heard <NpcName>Ben</> can get you the good stuff, even rare finds, but he doesn’t travel much anymore.//I can’t run my business based on <NpcName>Ben’s</> moods.

Text.SourceString: Coffee is the perfect drink for people-watching.//It’s a great excuse to sit and observe all the interesting things that are going on.
Text.LocalizedString: Coffee is the perfect drink for people-watching.//It’s a great excuse to sit and observe all the interesting things that are going on.

Text.SourceString: That’s how I fell in love with it – coffee.//<portrait=normal>Well, and people-watching.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s how I fell in love with it – coffee.//<portrait=normal>Well, and people-watching.

Text.SourceString: I’ve always loved the idea of running my own coffee shop, and now I get to do it here, where I can really get to know my customers.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve always loved the idea of running my own coffee shop, and now I get to do it here, where I can really get to know my customers.

Text.SourceString: I’ve met interesting folks here…through coffee.//<portrait=happy>A hunter, some scientists, a new farmer escaping the city life. *winks*
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve met interesting folks here…through coffee.//<portrait=happy>A hunter, some scientists, a new farmer escaping the city life. *winks*

Text.SourceString: I knew I’d enjoy living in an inn. I enjoy any kind of shared living arrangement.
Text.LocalizedString: I knew I’d enjoy living in an inn. I enjoy any kind of shared living arrangement.

Text.SourceString: I meet so many interesting people here. One of the tenants has a pet lobster.//<portrait=concerned>A lobster, yeah. You don’t see that every day.
Text.LocalizedString: I meet so many interesting people here. One of the tenants has a pet lobster.//<portrait=concerned>A lobster, yeah. You don’t see that every day.

Text.SourceString: Good thing I found this place. Renting one room is much cheaper than renting a whole house.
Text.LocalizedString: Good thing I found this place. Renting one room is much cheaper than renting a whole house.

Text.SourceString: Plus, I think I’d get really lonely if I lived in a house all by myself.//<portrait=sad>My fire would go out so fast…
Text.LocalizedString: Plus, I think I’d get really lonely if I lived in a house all by myself.//<portrait=sad>My fire would go out so fast…

Text.SourceString: Let’s be real. We all picked Coral Island partly because it was once such a lively place.//<portrait=sad>All the tourists… The business potential was on another level. Until the oil spill took it all away. *sighs*
Text.LocalizedString: Let’s be real. We all picked Coral Island partly because it was once such a lively place.//<portrait=sad>All the tourists… The business potential was on another level. Until the oil spill took it all away. *sighs*

Text.SourceString: Well, I guess not for you. It was your family’s farm you moved to, wasn’t it?//<portrait=happy>I guess you’re pretty much local.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, I guess not for you. It was your family’s farm you moved to, wasn’t it?//<portrait=happy>I guess you’re pretty much local.

Text.SourceString: I owe the twins a lot – not financially.//<portrait=sad>Well, sometimes financially. They’re lenient about the rent, and I’m thankful for that.
Text.LocalizedString: I owe the twins a lot – not financially.//<portrait=sad>Well, sometimes financially. They’re lenient about the rent, and I’m thankful for that.

Text.SourceString: It isn’t exactly raining money at the coffee shop right now. And gosh, the expenses don’t quit. Rent, beans, staff, <Italic>my</> rent. Gosh!//<portrait=sad>Running the shop is so expensive, sometimes I think about giving it up.
Text.LocalizedString: It isn’t exactly raining money at the coffee shop right now. And gosh, the expenses don’t quit. Rent, beans, staff, <Italic>my</> rent. Gosh!//<portrait=sad>Running the shop is so expensive, sometimes I think about giving it up.

Text.SourceString: I feel for the people here – before the Coffee Corner arrived. They had to go so far to get a <Italic>good</> cup of coffee.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel for the people here – before the Coffee Corner arrived. They had to go so far to get a <Italic>good</> cup of coffee.

Text.SourceString: It reminds me of my days in San Franciskyo. Not the bad coffee, the opposite, actually.//<portrait=happy>That place had so many good shops. I never had to walk more than thirty minutes to find one.
Text.LocalizedString: It reminds me of my days in San Franciskyo. Not the bad coffee, the opposite, actually.//<portrait=happy>That place had so many good shops. I never had to walk more than thirty minutes to find one.

Text.SourceString: Rent for my shop in Starlet Town is cheap.//<portrait=sad>So number-wise, it should have been a low-risk move to start my business here. You’d think, right? But nope.
Text.LocalizedString: Rent for my shop in Starlet Town is cheap.//<portrait=sad>So number-wise, it should have been a low-risk move to start my business here. You’d think, right? But nope.

Text.SourceString: Sales here aren’t too hot.//<portrait=sad>Even covering the relatively cheap rent is a struggle sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: Sales here aren’t too hot.//<portrait=sad>Even covering the relatively cheap rent is a struggle sometimes.

Text.SourceString: I must admit starting a business wasn’t as easy as I thought.//<portrait=concerned>Gotta miss the times when all I had to worry about was being a barista and making coffee.
Text.LocalizedString: I must admit starting a business wasn’t as easy as I thought.//<portrait=concerned>Gotta miss the times when all I had to worry about was being a barista and making coffee.

Text.SourceString: You gotta look in the mirror in the morning and like what you see. That’s what <Italic>living</> is all about.//Wear something that makes you feel good. Every day is a new day.
Text.LocalizedString: You gotta look in the mirror in the morning and like what you see. That’s what <Italic>living</> is all about.//Wear something that makes you feel good. Every day is a new day.

Text.SourceString: I put effort into what I wear every day. Yes, I do.//<portrait=happy>So what if we have nowhere to go? We gotta be happy with ourselves <Italic>for</> ourselves. Look good, feel good, right?
Text.LocalizedString: I put effort into what I wear every day. Yes, I do.//<portrait=happy>So what if we have nowhere to go? We gotta be happy with ourselves <Italic>for</> ourselves. Look good, feel good, right?

Text.SourceString: Silk clothing is good for this weather. Super breathable, good for your skin.//Gotta make sure your skin – your body – can breathe.//<portrait=happy>A silk pillowcase is a good idea too. It’s good for your hair.
Text.LocalizedString: Silk clothing is good for this weather. Super breathable, good for your skin.//Gotta make sure your skin – your body – can breathe.//<portrait=happy>A silk pillowcase is a good idea too. It’s good for your hair.

Text.SourceString: Silk clothing is good for this weather. Super breathable, good for your skin.//Gotta make sure your skin – your body – can breathe in this heat.//<portrait=happy>A silk pillowcase is a good idea too. It’s good for your hair.
Text.LocalizedString: Silk clothing is good for this weather. Super breathable, good for your skin.//Gotta make sure your skin – your body – can breathe in this heat.//<portrait=happy>A silk pillowcase is a good idea too. It’s good for your hair.

Text.SourceString: When I get myself a new outfit, yeah, it isn’t cheap, but the way I see it is this is what I wear.//This is how my body will feel for a lot of hours in the day, and you gotta consider that to be a priority, right?
Text.LocalizedString: When I get myself a new outfit, yeah, it isn’t cheap, but the way I see it is this is what I wear.//This is how my body will feel for a lot of hours in the day, and you gotta consider that to be a priority, right?

Text.SourceString: I don’t know where you got that outfit, but it looks great on you.//<portrait=happy>Good quality fabric, I can tell. Looks warm as heck. Is it a wool blend?
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know where you got that outfit, but it looks great on you.//<portrait=happy>Good quality fabric, I can tell. Looks warm as heck. Is it a wool blend?

Text.SourceString: I don’t know where you got that outfit, but it looks great on you.//<portrait=happy>Good quality fabric, I can tell. Nice. Very <Italic>summery</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know where you got that outfit, but it looks great on you.//<portrait=happy>Good quality fabric, I can tell. Nice. Very <Italic>summery</>.

Text.SourceString: The White Flamingo has this shirt I want, but it’s way too expensive.//Maybe I’ll save up for it.
Text.LocalizedString: The White Flamingo has this shirt I want, but it’s way too expensive.//Maybe I’ll save up for it.

Text.SourceString: Welcome to Raja Coffee, where we serve only the finest artisanal brews.//<portrait=annoyed>Yes, I am aware that we’re next door to a tavern.//Life’s full of little ironies, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: Welcome to Raja Coffee, where we serve only the finest artisanal brews.//<portrait=annoyed>Yes, I am aware that we’re next door to a tavern.//Life’s full of little ironies, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: You know, every time you walk into the shop, my day just seems a bit brighter.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, every time you walk into the shop, my day just seems a bit brighter.

Text.SourceString: You have a knack for making people feel comfortable.//It’s a rare and beautiful trait.
Text.LocalizedString: You have a knack for making people feel comfortable.//It’s a rare and beautiful trait.

Text.SourceString: You look absolutely stunning, <PlayerName>$Player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: You look absolutely stunning, <PlayerName>$Player</>.

Text.SourceString: I just want to say, your smile tops my list of favorite things.
Text.LocalizedString: I just want to say, your smile tops my list of favorite things.

Text.SourceString: I can’t seem to get you out of my head lately.//When I try to focus, there you are again. Your smile, your laugh, the way your eyes light up when you talk about something you love.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t seem to get you out of my head lately.//When I try to focus, there you are again. Your smile, your laugh, the way your eyes light up when you talk about something you love.

Text.SourceString: It’s…quite distracting, but in the best possible way.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s…quite distracting, but in the best possible way.

Text.SourceString: You see this espresso machine? It’s a masterpiece, cost me a fortune.//<portrait=happy>I mean, I was practically living off bread for a whole season because of it, but hey, quality matters, right?
Text.LocalizedString: You see this espresso machine? It’s a masterpiece, cost me a fortune.//<portrait=happy>I mean, I was practically living off bread for a whole season because of it, but hey, quality matters, right?

Text.SourceString: Ever tried baking bread?//<portrait=sad>I gave it a shot yesterday, and let’s just say the bakery has nothing to worry about.
Text.LocalizedString: Ever tried baking bread?//<portrait=sad>I gave it a shot yesterday, and let’s just say the bakery has nothing to worry about.

Text.SourceString: The only good thing about Winter is how it makes people crave a warm, comforting cup of joe.
Text.LocalizedString: The only good thing about Winter is how it makes people crave a warm, comforting cup of joe.

Text.SourceString: Winter’s harsh this year.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter’s harsh this year.

Text.SourceString: I tried making snow coffee once.//<portrait=annoyed>Let’s just say it was an…interesting experiment. Yeah, no…
Text.LocalizedString: I tried making snow coffee once.//<portrait=annoyed>Let’s just say it was an…interesting experiment. Yeah, no…

Text.SourceString: I’m not usually a fan of the cold, but there’s something about seeing the first snowfall that makes Winter a bit more bearable.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not usually a fan of the cold, but there’s something about seeing the first snowfall that makes Winter a bit more bearable.

Text.SourceString: But that’s it. It’s downhill after this, coldness all the way to Spring.
Text.LocalizedString: But that’s it. It’s downhill after this, coldness all the way to Spring.

Text.SourceString: This scarf is my favorite piece of clothing. It’s by Lewis Button, you know.//Truly the finest cashmere out there.//<portrait=sad>It’s really warm, though, so unless it’s freezing like now, I can’t wear it.
Text.LocalizedString: This scarf is my favorite piece of clothing. It’s by Lewis Button, you know.//Truly the finest cashmere out there.//<portrait=sad>It’s really warm, though, so unless it’s freezing like now, I can’t wear it.

Text.SourceString: Oh, just a heads-up. The <Italic>s</> in “Lewis” is silent.//Yeah, it’s a common mistake.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, just a heads-up. The <Italic>s</> in “Lewis” is silent.//Yeah, it’s a common mistake.

Text.SourceString: Some folks come in here just for the muffins, but I think there’s magic in good coffee and conversation.
Text.LocalizedString: Some folks come in here just for the muffins, but I think there’s magic in good coffee and conversation.

Text.SourceString: That’s what I want this place to be about.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s what I want this place to be about.

Text.SourceString: Our muffins are some of our bestsellers.//I’ve been considering adding some variations, thinking it might boost our sales. Yeah, nah! It didn’t.
Text.LocalizedString: Our muffins are some of our bestsellers.//I’ve been considering adding some variations, thinking it might boost our sales. Yeah, nah! It didn’t.

Text.SourceString: I’ve tried adding various ingredients – berries, bananas, nuts, fish, pumpkin, raisins…//<portrait=surprised>Yeah, raisins! Don’t make that face. It was as bad as it sounds.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve tried adding various ingredients – berries, bananas, nuts, fish, pumpkin, raisins…//<portrait=surprised>Yeah, raisins! Don’t make that face. It was as bad as it sounds.

Text.SourceString: I like coming here before heading to work.//<portrait=normal>I don’t need to open the shop today. My staff can handle it.
Text.LocalizedString: I like coming here before heading to work.//<portrait=normal>I don’t need to open the shop today. My staff can handle it.

Text.SourceString: This is an excellent spot for reading, isn’t it? A lot of bugs, oh yeah, but it’s <Italic>totally</> worth it.//<portrait=normal>Wearing long pants also helps. That, and <NpcName>Suki’s</> all-natural bug repellent.
Text.LocalizedString: This is an excellent spot for reading, isn’t it? A lot of bugs, oh yeah, but it’s <Italic>totally</> worth it.//<portrait=normal>Wearing long pants also helps. That, and <NpcName>Suki’s</> all-natural bug repellent.

Text.SourceString: Are you here to read too?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you here to read too?

Text.SourceString: I tried shaking the coconut trees in front of the inn. I saw you do it some time ago, so thought I’d give it a try, but nothing fell off.//<portrait=sad>I guess they weren’t ready for harvest yet.
Text.LocalizedString: I tried shaking the coconut trees in front of the inn. I saw you do it some time ago, so thought I’d give it a try, but nothing fell off.//<portrait=sad>I guess they weren’t ready for harvest yet.

Text.SourceString: Unless I did it wrong. Is there a <Italic>right</> way to shake coconut trees?
Text.LocalizedString: Unless I did it wrong. Is there a <Italic>right</> way to shake coconut trees?

Text.SourceString: I saw <NpcName>Betty</> filling up the bird feeder in Garden Lane yesterday. She’s there every Monday like clockwork, never misses a week.//I also see <NpcName>Noah</> there <Italic>occasionally</>. Yeah, only occasionally. Not always.
Text.LocalizedString: I saw <NpcName>Betty</> filling up the bird feeder in Garden Lane yesterday. She’s there every Monday like clockwork, never misses a week.//I also see <NpcName>Noah</> there <Italic>occasionally</>. Yeah, only occasionally. Not always.

Text.SourceString: Well, I guess I’m the same, except I just chill, perfecting the art of being a freeloader.//<portrait=normal>I don’t do anything as nice as what <NpcName>Betty</> does.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, I guess I’m the same, except I just chill, perfecting the art of being a freeloader.//<portrait=normal>I don’t do anything as nice as what <NpcName>Betty</> does.

Text.SourceString: I saw <NpcName>Betty</> filling up the bird feeder in Garden Lane yesterday. She’s there every Monday like clockwork, never misses a week.//I also see <NpcName>Noah</> there <Italic>occasionally</>. Yeah, only occasionally. Not always.
Text.LocalizedString: I saw <NpcName>Betty</> filling up the bird feeder in Garden Lane yesterday. She’s there every Monday like clockwork, never misses a week.//I also see <NpcName>Noah</> there <Italic>occasionally</>. Yeah, only occasionally. Not always.

Text.SourceString: Well, I guess I’m the same, except I just chill, perfecting the art of being a freeloader.//<portrait=normal>I don’t do anything as nice as what <NpcName>Betty</> does.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, I guess I’m the same, except I just chill, perfecting the art of being a freeloader.//<portrait=normal>I don’t do anything as nice as what <NpcName>Betty</> does.

Text.SourceString: There’s a <Italic>buttload</> of beetles and crickets around here, which isn’t exactly ideal.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s a <Italic>buttload</> of beetles and crickets around here, which isn’t exactly ideal.

Text.SourceString: Last Summer, I spotted a very fancy blue butterfly. It was captivating.//<portrait=happy>Oh, not here! You won’t find them here. It was over by the lake.
Text.LocalizedString: Last Summer, I spotted a very fancy blue butterfly. It was captivating.//<portrait=happy>Oh, not here! You won’t find them here. It was over by the lake.

Text.SourceString: I’ve considered cutting back on the gold-dusted doughnuts with my afternoon tea, but they’re just so…shiny!
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve considered cutting back on the gold-dusted doughnuts with my afternoon tea, but they’re just so…shiny!

Text.SourceString: I’ve tried budgeting, oh yeah. But it’s like my money has legs.//<portrait=sad>It just walks away, especially when I see fancy new silk shirts or a loveseat.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve tried budgeting, oh yeah. But it’s like my money has legs.//<portrait=sad>It just walks away, especially when I see fancy new silk shirts or a loveseat.

Text.SourceString: It’s worth it. I deserve a little treat.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s worth it. I deserve a little treat.

Text.SourceString: Once, someone gifted me a fish. Wait – was it you?//<portrait=happy>Ah, it <Italic>was</> you, wasn’t it? You rascal! Always with the surprises.//<portrait=annoyed>Oh, was it actually <NpcName>Mark</>? Huh. I can’t remember.
Text.LocalizedString: Once, someone gifted me a fish. Wait – was it you?//<portrait=happy>Ah, it <Italic>was</> you, wasn’t it? You rascal! Always with the surprises.//<portrait=annoyed>Oh, was it actually <NpcName>Mark</>? Huh. I can’t remember.

Text.SourceString: Anyway, I attempted to create a tuna glaze out of it. Yuck. It was <Italic>unappetizing</>.//In fact, it turned out to be even more disgusting than the fish itself.
Text.LocalizedString: Anyway, I attempted to create a tuna glaze out of it. Yuck. It was <Italic>unappetizing</>.//In fact, it turned out to be even more disgusting than the fish itself.

Text.SourceString: An outdoor event like live music or poetry readings could be a nice way to bring the community together to enjoy the beautiful Summer, yeah?
Text.LocalizedString: An outdoor event like live music or poetry readings could be a nice way to bring the community together to enjoy the beautiful Summer, yeah?

Text.SourceString: Oh yes, we do have the Animal Festival coming up soon.//Good thought!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh yes, we do have the Animal Festival coming up soon.//Good thought!

Text.SourceString: It’s all about the <Italic>threads</>, my friend. You can tell a lot about a person by their shoes.//<portrait=happy>If they’re shiny, they're going places.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s all about the <Italic>threads</>, my friend. You can tell a lot about a person by their shoes.//<portrait=happy>If they’re shiny, they're going places.

Text.SourceString: Never settle, <PlayerName>$Player</>. You don’t want to be the person who ended up with good when they could’ve had great.//<portrait=happy>Now, can I get you some great coffee?
Text.LocalizedString: Never settle, <PlayerName>$Player</>. You don’t want to be the person who ended up with good when they could’ve had great.//<portrait=happy>Now, can I get you some great coffee?

Text.SourceString: I spotted this new silk scarf at White Flamingo.//<portrait=concerned>It’s a bit on the pricey side, but the feel of it… So light and airy, just what I need for this Summer heat.
Text.LocalizedString: I spotted this new silk scarf at White Flamingo.//<portrait=concerned>It’s a bit on the pricey side, but the feel of it… So light and airy, just what I need for this Summer heat.

Text.SourceString: Hopefully, tomorrow’s weather will be as clear as today’s.//I’m planning to have my coffee by the creek in Garden Lane.
Text.LocalizedString: Hopefully, tomorrow’s weather will be as clear as today’s.//I’m planning to have my coffee by the creek in Garden Lane.

Text.SourceString: Can you believe I’m diving back into <Italic>Then There Were Bagels</> by Agatha Christine? It’s all about ten strangers stranded on an island with a mountain of bagels.//<portrait=concerned>I’ve read it at least five times now. Such a classic read.
Text.LocalizedString: Can you believe I’m diving back into <Italic>Then There Were Bagels</> by Agatha Christine? It’s all about ten strangers stranded on an island with a mountain of bagels.//<portrait=concerned>I’ve read it at least five times now. Such a classic read.

Text.SourceString: The mayor was telling me about your grandparents being old-timers around here. Is it true?//You must have a lot of memories of this place.
Text.LocalizedString: The mayor was telling me about your grandparents being old-timers around here. Is it true?//You must have a lot of memories of this place.

Text.SourceString: There’s something special about childhood memories. They linger.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s something special about childhood memories. They linger.

Special.SourceString: Yes, my fondest memories were made here.
Special.LocalizedString: Yes, my fondest memories were made here.

Text.SourceString: Oh well. Some memories are like that. They get blurry over time.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh well. Some memories are like that. They get blurry over time.

Text.SourceString: Two cats, huh? They had the place for it.//<portrait=normal>The cats must have had a lot of fun running around the farm.
Text.LocalizedString: Two cats, huh? They had the place for it.//<portrait=normal>The cats must have had a lot of fun running around the farm.

Special.SourceString: The only thing I remember is that they had two cats.
Special.LocalizedString: The only thing I remember is that they had two cats.

Text.SourceString: I love waking up at sunrise. The soothing light of a Fall morning is truly something.//<portrait=happy>I recommend it.
Text.LocalizedString: I love waking up at sunrise. The soothing light of a Fall morning is truly something.//<portrait=happy>I recommend it.

Text.SourceString: Oh, the music festival in Flower Valley? It’s next week, yeah?//<portrait=sad>The lineup looks good, but I don’t think I’ll go. Yeah, no. I’m just not in the mood.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, the music festival in Flower Valley? It’s next week, yeah?//<portrait=sad>The lineup looks good, but I don’t think I’ll go. Yeah, no. I’m just not in the mood.

Text.SourceString: I’m going to be doing my reading indoors now.//It’s much too cold to relax outside.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to be doing my reading indoors now.//It’s much too cold to relax outside.

Text.SourceString: I tried to catch a snowflake on my tongue this morning, bleh!//<portrait=annoyed>Ended up nearly swallowing a whole snowball. Not the breakfast I had in mind.
Text.LocalizedString: I tried to catch a snowflake on my tongue this morning, bleh!//<portrait=annoyed>Ended up nearly swallowing a whole snowball. Not the breakfast I had in mind.

Text.SourceString: Slipped on the ice right outside the shop this morning.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, I didn’t spill my coffee. Yeah, no. Now, that would have been a tragedy!
Text.LocalizedString: Slipped on the ice right outside the shop this morning.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, I didn’t spill my coffee. Yeah, no. Now, that would have been a tragedy!

Text.SourceString: It kind of smells in here, doesn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: It kind of smells in here, doesn’t it?

Text.SourceString: I told <NpcName>Mark</> about opening a pet café. Now, that’s a good idea!//You serve coffee and let people chill with the animals. Petflix and chill.//<portrait=annoyed>He said no.
Text.LocalizedString: I told <NpcName>Mark</> about opening a pet café. Now, that’s a good idea!//You serve coffee and let people chill with the animals. Petflix and chill.//<portrait=annoyed>He said no.

Text.SourceString: My task today is to mop this place, keeping it clean for my furry friends here.
Text.LocalizedString: My task today is to mop this place, keeping it clean for my furry friends here.

Text.SourceString: Watch out for the puddles over there. It isn’t, errr, water.//<portrait=sad>Somebody had an accident.
Text.LocalizedString: Watch out for the puddles over there. It isn’t, errr, water.//<portrait=sad>Somebody had an accident.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Mark</> has demoted me to mop duty now.//He revoked my litter-cleaning privileges after that one incident.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Mark</> has demoted me to mop duty now.//He revoked my litter-cleaning privileges after that one incident.

Text.SourceString: I mean, who knew you could create a litter box sandstorm just by using a leaf blower for quick cleaning?//<portrait=annoyed>Live and learn, I guess.
Text.LocalizedString: I mean, who knew you could create a litter box sandstorm just by using a leaf blower for quick cleaning?//<portrait=annoyed>Live and learn, I guess.

Text.SourceString: How much do you think it costs to run this place for a year? It can’t be cheap.
Text.LocalizedString: How much do you think it costs to run this place for a year? It can’t be cheap.

Text.SourceString: This place has an odd collection of books. I found one on aliens, one with cookie recipes, one about horses, even one on giant crops.//<portrait=happy>Yeah, no, it’s definitely a quite diverse collection.
Text.LocalizedString: This place has an odd collection of books. I found one on aliens, one with cookie recipes, one about horses, even one on giant crops.//<portrait=happy>Yeah, no, it’s definitely a quite diverse collection.

Text.SourceString: Welcome, welcome! It’s nice of you to stop by, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//<portrait=happy>How I’ve missed you!
Text.LocalizedString: Welcome, welcome! It’s nice of you to stop by, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//<portrait=happy>How I’ve missed you!

Text.SourceString: I was wondering when I’d be seeing you again.
Text.LocalizedString: I was wondering when I’d be seeing you again.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been reading <Italic>The Never-Ending Search for Giant Crops</>. Is that a thing?//<portrait=surprised>Do you have giant crops on your farm?
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been reading <Italic>The Never-Ending Search for Giant Crops</>. Is that a thing?//<portrait=surprised>Do you have giant crops on your farm?

Text.SourceString: Wow, really? That’s fascinating!
Text.LocalizedString: Wow, really? That’s fascinating!

Text.SourceString: Oh yeah! Imagine veggies and fruits the size of a cow, if not bigger!//<portrait=happy>Sounds strange, but giant crops are a real thing, according to some of the books here. Cool, right?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh yeah! Imagine veggies and fruits the size of a cow, if not bigger!//<portrait=happy>Sounds strange, but giant crops are a real thing, according to some of the books here. Cool, right?

Text.SourceString: Oh, really? Well, that’s a bit of a letdown.//<portrait=sad>I suppose not everything you read should be taken at face value!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, really? Well, that’s a bit of a letdown.//<portrait=sad>I suppose not everything you read should be taken at face value!

Text.SourceString: Have you read the book <Italic>Extraterrestrial Encounters</>? <NPCName>Alice</> lent it to me one time.//<portrait=surprised>It’s about supposed alien sightings. Yeah, no kidding.//<portrait=normal>Do you believe in aliens?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you read the book <Italic>Extraterrestrial Encounters</>? <NPCName>Alice</> lent it to me one time.//<portrait=surprised>It’s about supposed alien sightings. Yeah, no kidding.//<portrait=normal>Do you believe in aliens?

Text.SourceString: Oh wow! I <Italic>do</> sound like <NpcName>Alice</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh wow! I <Italic>do</> sound like <NpcName>Alice</>.

Text.SourceString: The universe is so big. It’s kinda hard not to wonder.
Text.LocalizedString: The universe is so big. It’s kinda hard not to wonder.

Text.SourceString: Most of what’s out there is hearsay. No, yeah.//So it makes sense if you’re a bit skeptical.
Text.LocalizedString: Most of what’s out there is hearsay. No, yeah.//So it makes sense if you’re a bit skeptical.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been working on this new blend. I call it the Java Extravaganza.//<portrait=happy>It’s more than just coffee, it’s a caffeinated journey!
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been working on this new blend. I call it the Java Extravaganza.//<portrait=happy>It’s more than just coffee, it’s a caffeinated journey!

Text.SourceString: Isn’t the decor in here fab? It has a vintage chic meets antique haven vibe.
Text.LocalizedString: Isn’t the decor in here fab? It has a vintage chic meets antique haven vibe.

Text.SourceString: I’m stepping up my sock game. Style’s not just about shoes and clothes.//<portrait=happy>I’m thinking cashmere-blend socks. <Italic>Beige</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m stepping up my sock game. Style’s not just about shoes and clothes.//<portrait=happy>I’m thinking cashmere-blend socks. <Italic>Beige</>.

Text.SourceString: Did you see the sunrise this morning? Just bursting with color!
Text.LocalizedString: Did you see the sunrise this morning? Just bursting with color!

Text.SourceString: I’m a human popsicle.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m a human popsicle.

Text.SourceString: It’s cold.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s cold.

Text.SourceString: Some of my coffee beans have traveled more than I have.//Imported straight from Patavia, it’s like a vacation in a cup.
